          <div class="update-components-text relative feed-shared-update-v2__commentary " dir="ltr">
<!---->
  <span class="break-words">
<!---->      <span><span dir="ltr">Unpopular opinion I’m guessing for LinkedIn:<br>Doing &gt; Knowing.<br><br>Confidence comes from action, not from information. Doing things that scare you and failing at them is a far better way to learn something new than reading about it, watching videos etc. In fact, I will go to the extent of saying that often researching too much about something leads to the classic overthinking &amp; inaction spiral. <br><br>The only way to stop that overthinking, procrastinating train that keeps us stuck in our comfort zone is to (a) sign up &amp; then (b) show up. Everything else can somehow be figured out on the go. <br><br>If you develop the habit of jumping into action, you will struggle more, you will fail more, you will look quite stupid in fact. But you will always grow faster in the process. <br><br>Stop the overthinking. <br>Sign up! <br>Show up! <br><br>P.S.: I don’t know how to surf. Tried it with <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ACoAAACN3DQBzTXVDoMOqmnhd-15E1KoKXVCJu8" data-attribute-index="0" data-entity-type="MINI_PROFILE">Kaushik Mukherjee</a> few weeks ago &amp; royally failed at it. The “stupid looking” pics are conveniently not being posted 🤣</span></span>
  </span>
</div>

      <span class="feed-shared-inline-show-more-text__see-more-text">…see more</span>
